WorldStage Newsonlin e– Lagos State Government has responded to enquiries on the status of First Cardiology Consultants, the hospital where Mallam Abba Kyari, the Chief of Staff to the President of Nigeria, died on Friday 17th April 2020 from complications in Coronavirus infection, saying it was accredited to treat the disease. A statement signed by Dr. Akin Abayomi, Commissioner for Health, Lagos State said, “This hospital is a Lagos State designated high care, biosecurity-compliant, COVID-19 facility, accredited by the Health Facility Management and Accreditation Agency (HEFAMAA) of the Lagos State Ministry of Health. “As a basis for accreditation, First Cardiology Consultants established a separate specialist wing with staff dedicated to the treatment of complicated cases of COVID-19, under the supervision of the Lagos State COVID-19 emergency response team.”